Might have been luck, but for me the advice of going to Thurgadin paid out. <p><img SRC="http://www.euphorion.org/sig/euph_zdd2.jpg"> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/useek9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seek 9</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 552<br> <font color=#333333>(5/31/02 2:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1309.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Gloves of Rallos Zek</span><hr size=1> I had very few problems getting components like these...even the harder to come by ones like Words of Bondage, Wing of Xegony, etc.<br>
<br>
- Tell your guildmates to keep an eye out for such components.   <br>
<br>
- Check every merchant in city zones about once a week, especially old world and Kunark's FV.   Really, you can check almost all merchants in a city zone in only a few minutes.    Freeport has a TON of merhants in NFP, WFP, EFP.<br>
<br>
- Always buy components that you see for sale (from PCs and NPCs), even if you won't be needing them for several levels.   In my 20s, I even bought things like Essence of Rathe and Words of Convocation, even though I would not need these until 40+.  Don't forget to buy extras as you will need to re-research spells to use as components for some spells in the next level (stupid chain research).<br>
Basically, if you do this, you will collect just about all you need. <p><u>Seek Pyremaker</u><br>
